<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-85-0114 </DOCNO><TEXT>When Secretary General M. Honecker visited Bonn on the 8th September 1987,an environmental protection agreement and a radiation protection agreementwere signed. The environmental agreement forms the basis of a comprehensiveexchange of information between experts of the two states and providesfor the prerequisites of joint pollution control measures. The radiationprotection convention mainly refers to regulations of the peaceful usesof nuclear energy. (CW)</TEXT></DOC>